FBIS3-58682 "drweu012_i_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 FRANCE Leotard Says Butrus-Ghali Requested Cot's Recall AU1801151194 Paris AFP in English 1459 GMT 18 Jan 94 AU1801151194 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Paris, Jan 18 (AFP) -- United Nations Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali has requested the recall of French General Jean Cot, commander of UN forces in former Yugoslavia, French Defence Minister Francois Leotard said Tuesday [18 January]. Butrus-Ghali made the call to Leotard, French President Francois Mitterrand and Prime Minister Edouard Balladur during a visit here last week, the minister said. Leotard was speaking at a luncheon of MPs of the governing majority at Balladur's residence here, participants said. One reported that Leotard said he had agreed to Butrus-Ghali's request, but set conditions. [passage omitted]
